  "prompt": "What is the main function of the rough endoplasmic reticulum?",
  "response": "The main function of the rough endoplasmic reticulum (RER) is to synthesize and process proteins. It is called \"rough\" because its surface is studded with ribosomes, which are the cellular machinery responsible for protein synthesis. The RER plays a crucial role in the production of proteins that are destined for secretion from the cell, incorporation into the cell membrane, or transport to other organelles such as lysosomes. Once synthesized by the ribosomes, these proteins enter the lumen of the RER, where they undergo folding, modification (such as glycosylation), and quality control to ensure proper structure and function before being transported to their final destinations. The RER is particularly important in cells that produce large amounts of proteins, such as those in the pancreas, liver, and immune system.",
